Research Overview

This folder contains all research, analysis, and conceptual groundwork for the BICOM-AI project.
It serves as the intellectual foundation of the system and guides all technical and business decisions.

The goal of this research is to ensure that BICOM-AI solves real-world business problems using practical, data-driven AI approaches.

Problem Definition

Modern businesses struggle with:

Interpreting large volumes of data

Making consistent strategic decisions

Forecasting risks and opportunities

Translating insights into actionable plans

BICOM-AI is designed to act as an AI executive, helping decision-makers think clearly, strategically, and proactively.

Target Users

This research focuses on the needs of:

Entrepreneurs and startup founders

Small and medium-sized business owners

Corporate managers and executives

Strategy and operations teams

Research Areas

Key research topics include:

Business strategy and decision science

Market analysis and competitive intelligence

Financial forecasting and risk assessment

AI-assisted planning and reasoning

Humanâ€“AI collaboration in leadership roles

Methodology

Research materials in this folder may include:

Case studies

Industry reports

Market trend analysis

Conceptual frameworks

Academic references

Notes and brainstorming documents

Output of This Folder

The research here informs:

System architecture

AI model design

Feature prioritization

Product roadmap

Ethical and practical constraints
